               <div class="col-md-6 lineup-artists">
                    <figure class="featured-image">
                        <img src="../images/roborace.jpg" alt="">
                                    <!-- <a href="#" class="box-link"> <img src="images/box.jpg" alt=""> </a> -->
                    </figure>                   	
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-6 lineup-artists-headline">
                    <h2 class="entry-title">Problem Statement</h2>
                    <font size="17">
                    Design and fabricate an autonomous or manual  vehicle capable of navigating efficently through all possible terrains like sand,pebbles,obstacles,bumpers,bridges,marbles,grease,inclines,dips,cliffs,ramps,banks,etc.The vehicle must be ab;e to effectively follow the path .The robots will be tested on speed and how well navigates through the defined path. </div>


                    </font>
                     <div class="col-md-6 lineup-artists-headline">
                    <h2 class="entry-title">Robot Specification</h2>
                    <font size="17">
                        <ol start type="value"=1>
                            <li>The maximum dimension of the robot can be 30 cm x 30 cm(l x b).</li>
                            <li>The robot may be wired or wireless.</li>
                            <li>The length of the wire (for wired robot) should be long enough to cover the whole track and wire should remain slack during complete run. </li>
                             <li>Max weight must not exceed 6kg.</li>
                             <li>The power supply can be maximum 24 volts.</li>
                             <li>Readymade toy car are not allowed.</li>
                             <li>Battery may be on-board or off-board.</li>
                             </ol>                              
                    <div class="col-md-6 lineup-artists-headline">
                    <h2 class="entry-title">Rules And Regulations</h2>

                      <ol start type="value"=1>
                        <li><p> Robots should be as per the given dimensions .</p></li>
                        <li><p> Each team can have maximum 3 members.Students from different institutes can form a team</p></li>
                        <b><li><p> No entry fee.</p></li></b>
                        <li><p> Each member of the team should carry identity card of his institution.</p></li>
                        <li><p> The robot should not damage the track.</p></li>
                        <li><p>The robot must not leave behind any of its parts during the run;else it will result in disqualification. </p></li>
                        <li><p>Unethical behaviour can lead to disqualification.Faculty - coordinators have all the rights to take final decision for any matter during the event </p>   </li>
                        <li><p>Certificates will be given to all the participants</p></li>
                        <li><p>The track would be constructed on ground and multiple obstacles(which will be revealed at the time of the event) will span the track</p></li>                 


                    </ol>
                    <h2 class="entry-title">Contact</h2>
                    <p><i class="fa fa-phone" aria-hidden="true"></i> Vivek : +91 84271 55574</p>
                    <button class="register p-3 btn btn-outline-info text-center justify-content-center">REGISTER FOR EVENTS</button>
